user-1-2-4                      Xerox Quintus Prolog User's Guide                        Section 1-2-4: Exiting PrologTo exit from the Prolog system, type 'halt.' at the top-level prompt, as shownbelow:            | ?- halt.The Prolog system will halt, a message will be displayed, and you will bereturned to your main operating system prompt, as shown below:            [ End of Prolog execution ]            <prompt>You now know the basics of Prolog and of the Xerox Quintus Prolog system.  Forinformation on additional commands, see {manual(user-2)}.  For a fuller summaryof Xerox Quintus Prolog , see the Syntax and Semantics chapters of the XeroxQuintus Prolog Reference Manual.